**Equicorrelation: Feasible Bounds and Construction.** Let $X,Y,Z$ have $\text{Corr}(X,Y)=\text{Corr}(X,Z)=\text{Corr}(Y,Z)=\rho$. \begin{enumerate}[label=(\alph{*})]\item What bounds must $\rho$ satisfy?

\item Given $\rho$ in the valid range, construct explicit random variables achieving this equicorrelation.

\item How does this generalise to $n$ variables with all pairwise correlations equal to $\rho$?\end{enumerate}

**Covariance of Order Statistics.** Let $X_{(1)}\leq X_{(2)}\leq\cdots\leq X_{(n)}$ be the order statistics of $n$ i.i.d.\ $\mathrm{Uniform}(0,1)$ random variables. \begin{enumerate}[label=(\alph{*})]\item Find $\mathbb{E}[X_{(k)}]$ for the $k$-th order statistic.

\item Find $\text{Cov}(X_{(1)}, X_{(n)})$ — the covariance of the minimum and maximum.

\item Are $X_{(1)}$ and $X_{(n)}$ positively or negatively correlated? Explain intuitively.\end{enumerate}
